      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 55,
      "message": "Is this combination of maxretries and retry timeout really enough to make any difference? The retry should cover the case when a PNF is e.g. restarting, and that can take up to 90 seconds. If only three retries are made and the initial retry timeout is only 5 secons, it will hardly retry long enough to cover this case.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3763,
        "name": "Henrik Andersson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "henrik.b.andersson@est.tech",
        "username": "elinuxhenrik"
      },
